> >We've seen examples of programs (a la CRACK) which will take given
> >input files (dictionaries) and attempt to break passwords... but I've
> >yet to see a program which will actually attempt to crack the DES
> >encryption itself.
> 
> >Are there some available for FTP?  
> 
> >(respond via email and I will summarize if there's interest)
> 
> Here is a sample
> char key[8]
> char *break(char text[9],crypt[9])
> {
>  for(key[0]=0;key[0]<128;key[0]
>  for (key[1]=0;key[1]<128;key[1]i++)
>    .....
>  for(key[7]=0;key[7]<128;key[7]++)
>    if(! bcmp(DES(key,text),crypt,8)) return(key);
> return(-1)
> }
> Write properly compile and run. Wait a while (say a million years on a
> good workstation) and there you have it. You might if you have a million
> dollars or so be able to cobble together some gates, etc to construct a
> special computer to run the above instead ( it is a simple program after
> all) and reduce that to a few hours or days, but I assumed that you have
> a workstation.

I wonder if there is any better methods? Maybe a crytographic method instead
of raw power :-)

Trefor S.
